pull.title: Disable wallet and address book Qt tests on macOS minimal platform
pull.body:
macOS minimal platform is frequently broken, and these are currently failing with Qt 5.11.1.

The tests do pass when run on the full cocoa platform (with `test_bitcoin-qt -platform cocoa`).

Stack trace from test crash: https://gist.github.com/ryanofsky/3401fb63c52d13d5585e7fc777361f1e

events.message:
Disable wallet and address book Qt tests on macOS minimal platform

macOS Qt minimal platform is frequently broken, and these are currently failing
with Qt 5.11.1.

The tests do pass when run on the full cocoa platform
(with `test_bitcoin-qt -platform cocoa`).

events.body: <!--e57a25ab6845829454e8d69fc972939a-->No more conflicts as of last run.

I did `make check` and `src/qt/test/test_bitcoin-qt -platform cocoa`, but it's still running `WalletTests` and `AddressBookTests`. Maybe I need a different `-platform` argument?

The test pass for me on macOS 10.13.6 with QT 5.11.1 via Homebrew, with and without this change.
@ryanofsky Could you address any comments/nits here and rebase if needed. I'd like to get this (or something equivalent) merged.

Updated 391cca51582269015f23bf931461160a111cc420 -> f7a533f17992e73ced6b57a9725997e040eeaa8a ([pr/fuqtmac.2](https://github.com/ryanofsky/bitcoin/commits/pr/fuqtmac.2) -> [pr/fuqtmac.3](https://github.com/ryanofsky/bitcoin/commits/pr/fuqtmac.3)) just fixing whitespace.

From comments above I guess fanquake could reproduce the test failures, and sjors couldn't, but I think it's best just to skip these tests on the uncommonly used minimal mac platform, rather than try to debug.

tACK f7a533f

`make check` is now fixed for me.

Updated f7a533f17992e73ced6b57a9725997e040eeaa8a -> a3197c5294df4711bab0ff6dcdd061ceab115c7d ([pr/fuqtmac.3](https://github.com/ryanofsky/bitcoin/commits/pr/fuqtmac.3) -> [pr/fuqtmac.4](https://github.com/ryanofsky/bitcoin/commits/pr/fuqtmac.4)) with spelling fix.

re-tACK a3197c5

Merged on top of https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/816fab9ccae568612d5ed90378b4587256925a1e and checked `make check -j6`.

Can't reproduce the error on macOS 10.14.
```
src/qt/test/test_bitcoin-qt -platform minimal
********* Start testing of URITests *********
Config: Using QtTest library 5.11.1, Qt 5.11.1 (x86_64-little_endian-lp64 shared (dynamic) release build; by Clang 9.1.0 (clang-902.0.39.2) (Apple))
...
```

I think this is ready for merge. It is platform specific and has tested acks from fanquake https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-428425974 https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-430841960 and IlyasRidhuan https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-431257781 and an untested ACK from jonasschnelli https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-430732185.

Sjors and promag have reported in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-419534656 and https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/14011#issuecomment-431380010 that they actually see tests passing without this change, so the issue does seem be a little unpredictable. But this is a good, safe fix for #14349, and also a prerequisite for #11625, which expands qt test coverage and exposes more problems with the qt mac minimal platform.
